            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EPrayer%20is%20the%20key%20that%20overcomes%20the%20enemy%20in%20battle.%20Hezekiah%20prayed%20on%20two%20different%20occasions%20and%20thus%20overcame%20tremendous%20struggles.%20First%2C%20he%20and%20Isaiah%20prayed%20against%20the%20invasion%20by%20Sennacherib%20(2%20Chronicles%2032%3A20)%2C%20and%20God%20sent%20His%20angel%20to%20completely%20destroy%20the%20enemy's%20army.%20Then%2C%20in%20a%20struggle%20for%20his%20life%2C%20Hezekiah%20sought%20God%2C%20and%20God%20healed%20him%20in%20answer%20to%20his%20prayer%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E(v.%2024).%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EManasseh%2C%20too%2C%20experienced%20the%20power%20of%20prayer%20to%20change%20a%20difficult%20situation.%20While%20in%20a%20Babylonian%20jail%2C%20he%20prayed%20to%20the%20Lord%2C%20and%20God%20miraculously%20delivered%20him%20and%20restored%20him%20to%20power.%20What%20powerful%20illustrations%20of%20prayer%20and%20its%20ability%20to%20release%20God's%20deliverance%20these%20examples%20are!%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EPaul%20understood%20this%20principle%20of%20prayer%20when%20he%20asked%20the%20Romans%20to%20struggle%20with%20him%20in%20prayer%20that%20he%20might%20be%20%22rescued%20from%20those%20in%20Judea%20who%20refuse%20to%20obey%20God%22%20(Romans%2015%3A31).%20David%20voiced%20a%20similar%20prayer%3A%20%22Protect%20me!%20Rescue%20my%20life%20from%20them!%20Do%20not%20let%20me%20be%20disgraced%2C%20for%20I%20trust%20in%20you%22%20(Psalm%2025%3A20).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EYour%20spiritual%20leaders%20need%20your%20prayers.%20Pray%20diligently%20today%20for%20them%20to%20be%20protected%2C%20fruitful%2C%20and%20refreshed.%20Your%20prayers%20may%20save%20their%20lives!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
            "id": "ot-passage",
            "type": "passage",
            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "2Chr.32:1-33:13",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3E2%20Chronicles%2032%3A1-33%3A13%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_32_1%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2232%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E2%20Chronicles%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E32%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EAssyria%20Invades%20Judah%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EAfter%20Hezekiah%20had%20faithfully%20carried%20out%20this%20work%2C%20King%20Sennacherib%20of%20Assyria%20invaded%20Judah.%20He%20laid%20siege%20to%20the%20fortified%20towns%2C%20giving%20orders%20for%20his%20army%20to%20break%20through%20their%20walls.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_32_2%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2232%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Hezekiah%20realized%20that%20Sennacherib%20also%20intended%20to%20attack%20Jerusalem%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_32_3%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2232%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3Ehe%20consulted%20with%20his%20officials%20and%20military%20advisers%2C%20and%20they%20decided%20to%20stop%20the%20flow%20of%20the%20springs%20outside%20the%20city.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_32_4%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2232%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20organized%20a%20huge%20work%20crew%20to%20stop%20the%20flow%20of%20the%20springs%2C%20cutting%20off%20the%20brook%20that%20ran%20through%20the%20fields.%20For%20they%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BWhy%20should%20the%20kings%20of%20Assyria%20come%20here%20and%20find%20plenty%20of%20water%3F%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_32_5%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2232%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Hezekiah%20worked%20hard%20at%20repairing%20all%20the%20broken%20sections%20of%20the%20wall%2C%20erecting%20towers%2C%20and%20constructing%20a%20second%20wall%20outside%20the%20first.%20He%20also%20reinforced%20the%20supporting%20terraces%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E32%3A5%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20millo.%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20meaning%20of%20the%20Hebrew%20is%20uncertain.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20in%20the%20City%20of%20David%20and%20manufactured%20large%20numbers%20of%20weapons%20and%20shields.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_32_6%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2232%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20appointed%20military%20officers%20over%20the%20people%20and%20assembled%20them%20before%20him%20in%20the%20square%20at%20the%20city%20gate.%20Then%20Hezekiah%20encouraged%20them%20by%20saying%3A%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_32_7%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2232%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BBe%20strong%20and%20courageous!%20Don%26%23x2019%3Bt%20be%20afraid%20or%20discouraged%20because%20of%20the%20king%20of%20Assyria%20or%20his%20mighty%20army%2C%20for%20there%20is%20a%20power%20far%20greater%20on%20our%20side!%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_32_8%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2232%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20may%20have%20a%20great%20army%2C%20but%20they%20are%20merely%20men.%20We%20have%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20our%20God%20to%20help%20us%20and%20to%20fight%20our%20battles%20for%20us!%26%23x201D%3B%20Hezekiah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20words%20greatly%20encouraged%20the%20people.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_32_9%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2232%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3ESennacherib%20Threatens%20Jerusalem%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EWhile%20King%20Sennacherib%20of%20Assyria%20was%20still%20besieging%20the%20town%20of%20Lachish%2C%20he%20sent%20his%20officers%20to%20Jerusalem%20with%20this%20message%20for%20Hezekiah%20and%20all%20the%20people%20in%20the%20city%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_32_10%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2232%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body-fl-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BThis%20is%20what%20King%20Sennacherib%20of%20Assyria%20says%3A%20What%20are%20you%20trusting%20in%20that%20makes%20you%20think%20you%20can%20survive%20my%20siege%20of%20Jerusalem%3F%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_32_11%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2232%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EHezekiah%20has%20said%2C%20%26%23x2018%3BThe%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20our%20God%20will%20rescue%20us%20from%20the%20king%20of%20Assyria.%26%23x2019%3B%20Surely%20Hezekiah%20is%20misleading%20you%2C%20sentencing%20you%20to%20death%20by%20famine%20and%20thirst!%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_32_12%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2232%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EDon%26%23x2019%3Bt%20you%20realize%20that%20Hezekiah%20is%20the%20very%20person%20who%20destroyed%20all%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20shrines%20and%20altars%3F%20He%20commanded%20Judah%20and%20Jerusalem%20to%20worship%20only%20at%20the%20altar%20at%20the%20Temple%20and%20to%20offer%20sacrifices%20on%20it%20alone.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_32_13%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2232%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BSurely%20you%20must%20realize%20what%20I%20and%20the%20other%20kings%20of%20Assyria%20before%20me%20have%20done%20to%20all%20the%20people%20of%20the%20earth!%20Were%20any%20of%20the%20gods%20of%20those%20nations%20able%20to%20rescue%20their%20people%20from%20my%20power%3F%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_32_14%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2232%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EWhich%20of%20their%20gods%20was%20able%20to%20rescue%20its%20people%20from%20the%20destructive%20power%20of%20my%20predecessors%3F%20What%20makes%20you%20think%20your%20God%20can%20rescue%20you%20from%20me%3F%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_32_15%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2232%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EDon%26%23x2019%3Bt%20let%20Hezekiah%20deceive%20you!%20Don%26%23x2019%3Bt%20let%20him%20fool%20you%20like%20this!%20I%20say%20it%20again%26%23x2014%3Bno%20god%20of%20any%20nation%20or%20kingdom%20has%20ever%20yet%20been%20able%20to%20rescue%20his%20people%20from%20me%20or%20my%20ancestors.%20How%20much%20less%20will%20your%20God%20rescue%20you%20from%20my%20power!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_32_16%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2232%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EAnd%20Sennacherib%26%23x2019%3Bs%20officers%20further%20mocked%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20God%20and%20his%20servant%20Hezekiah%2C%20heaping%20insult%20upon%20insult.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_32_17%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2232%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20king%20also%20sent%20letters%20scorning%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20the%20God%20of%20Israel.%20He%20wrote%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BJust%20as%20the%20gods%20of%20all%20the%20other%20nations%20failed%20to%20rescue%20their%20people%20from%20my%20power%2C%20so%20the%20God%20of%20Hezekiah%20will%20also%20fail.%26%23x201D%3B%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_32_18%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2232%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20Assyrian%20officials%20who%20brought%20the%20letters%20shouted%20this%20in%20Hebrew%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E32%3A18%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ein%20the%20dialect%20of%20Judah.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20to%20the%20people%20gathered%20on%20the%20walls%20of%20the%20city%2C%20trying%20to%20terrify%20them%20so%20it%20would%20be%20easier%20to%20capture%20the%20city.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_32_19%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2232%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EThese%20officers%20talked%20about%20the%20God%20of%20Jerusalem%20as%20though%20he%20were%20one%20of%20the%20pagan%20gods%2C%20made%20by%20human%20hands.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_32_20%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2232%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20King%20Hezekiah%20and%20the%20prophet%20Isaiah%20son%20of%20Amoz%20cried%20out%20in%20prayer%20to%20God%20in%20heaven.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_32_21%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2232%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3EAnd%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20sent%20an%20angel%20who%20destroyed%20the%20Assyrian%20army%20with%20all%20its%20commanders%20and%20officers.%20So%20Sennacherib%20was%20forced%20to%20return%20home%20in%20disgrace%20to%20his%20own%20land.%20And%20when%20he%20entered%20the%20temple%20of%20his%20god%2C%20some%20of%20his%20own%20sons%20killed%20him%20there%20with%20a%20sword.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_32_22%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2232%22%20vn%3D%2222%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3EThat%20is%20how%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20rescued%20Hezekiah%20and%20the%20people%20of%20Jerusalem%20from%20King%20Sennacherib%20of%20Assyria%20and%20from%20all%20the%20others%20who%20threatened%20them.%20So%20there%20was%20peace%20throughout%20the%20land.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_32_23%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2232%22%20vn%3D%2223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E23%3C%2Fspan%3EFrom%20then%20on%20King%20Hezekiah%20became%20highly%20respected%20among%20all%20the%20surrounding%20nations%2C%20and%20many%20gifts%20for%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20arrived%20at%20Jerusalem%2C%20with%20valuable%20presents%20for%20King%20Hezekiah%2C%20too.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_32_24%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2232%22%20vn%3D%2224%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EHezekiah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Sickness%20and%20Recovery%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E24%3C%2Fspan%3EAbout%20that%20time%20Hezekiah%20became%20deathly%20ill.%20He%20prayed%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20who%20healed%20him%20and%20gave%20him%20a%20miraculous%20sign.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_32_25%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2232%22%20vn%3D%2225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E25%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20Hezekiah%20did%20not%20respond%20appropriately%20to%20the%20kindness%20shown%20him%2C%20and%20he%20became%20proud.%20So%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20anger%20came%20against%20him%20and%20against%20Judah%20and%20Jerusalem.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_32_26%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2232%22%20vn%3D%2226%22%3E%3Cspan%20